Interactive fetch-edit-push cycle for a Confluence page

Usage: edit <ID>

Arguments:
  <ID>  Confluence page ID (e.g., 12345678)

Options:
  -h, --help  Print help


================================================================================

omni-dev atlassian confluence read - Fetches a Confluence page and outputs it as JFM markdown or ADF JSON

Fetches a Confluence page and outputs it as JFM markdown or ADF JSON

Usage: read [OPTIONS] <ID>

Arguments:
  <ID>  Confluence page ID (e.g., 12345678)

Options:
  -o, --output <OUTPUT>  Output file (writes to stdout if omitted)
      --format <FORMAT>  Output format [default: jfm] [possible values: jfm, adf]
  -h, --help             Print help (see more with '--help')


================================================================================

omni-dev atlassian confluence search - Searches Confluence pages using CQL

Searches Confluence pages using CQL

Usage: search [OPTIONS]

Options:
      --cql <CQL>        Raw CQL query string (e.g., "space = ENG AND title ~ 'architecture'")
      --space <SPACE>    Filter by space key
      --title <TITLE>    Filter by title (substring match)
      --limit <LIMIT>    Maximum number of results, 0 for unlimited (default: 25) [default: 25]
  -o, --output <OUTPUT>  Output format [default: table] [possible values: table, json, yaml]
  -h, --help             Print help (see more with '--help')


================================================================================

omni-dev atlassian confluence write - Pushes content to a Confluence page

Pushes content to a Confluence page

Usage: write [OPTIONS] <ID> [FILE]

Arguments:
  <ID>    Confluence page ID (e.g., 12345678)
  [FILE]  Input file (reads from stdin if omitted or "-")

Options:
      --format <FORMAT>  Input format [default: jfm] [possible values: jfm, adf]
      --force            Skips the confirmation prompt
      --dry-run          Shows what would change without writing
  -h, --help             Print help (see more with '--help')


